      "comment_id" : 81130813,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@lyuboslavkanev The problem is that having the generic type in Java isn&#39;t enough to actually create objects based on that type; not even an array (which is ridiculous, because that should work for <i>any</i> type). All that can be done with it, as far as I can see, is casting. In fact, to even create objects of the type, you need to have the actual <code>Class</code> object, which seems to be completely impossible to derive from the generic type. The reason for this, as I said, is that the whole construction is fake; it&#39;s all just stored as Object internally."
    } ],
