    "creation_date" : 1453916468,
    "answer_id" : 35044382,
    "question_id" : 4042434,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use the <code>toArray()</code> method for <code>List</code>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ArrayList&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n\nlist.add(\"apple\");\nlist.add(\"banana\");\n\nString[] array = list.toArray(new String[list.size()]);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Or you can manually add the elements to an array:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ArrayList&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n\nlist.add(\"apple\");\nlist.add(\"banana\");\n\nString[] array = new String[list.size()];\n\nfor (int i = 0; i &lt; list.size(); i++) {\n    array[i] = list.get(i);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Hope this helps!</p>\n"
  }, {
